1
00:00:21,155 --> 00:00:23,123
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

2
00:00:23,123 --> 00:00:25,020
<i>MAN 1 [ON TV] :
Wrong, as usual.</i>

3
00:00:25,020 --> 00:00:28,321
<i>The United States' lack of action
in Eastern Europe...</i>

4
00:00:28,321 --> 00:00:32,933
<i>...proves that the Soviet Union's aggression
at the Afghan border...</i>

5
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:36,264
<i>...will not be opposed publicly
by the United States.</i>

6
00:00:36,264 --> 00:00:37,699
[WHISTLING STOPS]

7
00:00:38,306 --> 00:00:43,642
<i>Issue: The Soviet Union continued
its recent series of military exercises...</i>

8
00:00:43,642 --> 00:00:47,042
<i>...conducting a bomb test today
in the Bering Sea...</i>

9
00:00:47,042 --> 00:00:51,151
<i>...just 1500 miles
off the southern coast of Alaska.</i>

10
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:55,688
<i>President Richard Nixon
issued this warning to the Soviets:</i>

11
00:00:55,688 --> 00:00:59,349
MAN 2:
The United States does not start fights.

12
00:00:59,349 --> 00:01:03,190
Let it be clear we maintain our strength...

13
00:01:03,190 --> 00:01:06,162
...in order to maintain peace...

14
00:01:06,162 --> 00:01:10,065
...so any adversary
should ask themselves:

15
00:01:10,065 --> 00:01:13,298
"Do the consequences
of attacking America...

16
00:01:13,298 --> 00:01:16,102
...outweigh the potential benefits?"

17
00:01:16,102 --> 00:01:18,905
As a result of the Soviet activity...

18
00:01:18,905 --> 00:01:21,878
...the watchdog group
of nuclear scientists...

19
00:01:21,878 --> 00:01:27,454
<i>...moved the Doomsday Clock
up to five minutes until midnight:</i>

20
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:31,922
destruction by nuclear war.

21
00:01:32,627 --> 00:01:34,322
<i>Question:</i>

22
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:37,120
On a scale of zero to 10,
zero meaning impossibility...

23
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:39,630
...10 meaning
complete metaphysical certitude...

24
00:01:39,630 --> 00:01:44,295
...what are the chances the Russians
will actually attack the United States?

25
00:01:44,295 --> 00:01:45,769
Pat Buchanan.

26
00:01:45,769 --> 00:01:47,271
Zero.

27
00:01:47,271 --> 00:01:50,070
The Soviets
would never risk going to war...

28
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:54,078
...when we have a walking nuclear deterrent
on our side.

29
00:01:54,078 --> 00:01:56,716
You're referring, of course,
to Dr. Manhattan...

30
00:01:56,716 --> 00:02:00,980
<i>...but does Dr. Manhattan's existence
guarantee world peace? Eleanor Clift.</i>

31
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:03,885
<i>Well, it hasn't
stopped the Soviet Union...</i>

32
00:02:03,885 --> 00:02:08,722
<i>...from stockpiling record amounts
of nuclear weapons.</i>

33
00:02:08,722 --> 00:02:10,591
You don't think it's all just posturing?

34
00:02:10,591 --> 00:02:12,357
Maybe the reason
why the Soviets...

35
00:02:12,357 --> 00:02:15,058
...are doing these bomb tests...

36
00:02:15,058 --> 00:02:19,605
...is because they feel threatened
by Dr. Manhattan. Of course.

37
00:02:20,174 --> 00:02:23,302
<i>Maybe the whole world feels like that.</i>

38
00:02:23,302 --> 00:02:25,139
[MTV THEME " MAN ON THE MOON"
PLAYS ON TV]

39
00:02:25,139 --> 00:02:27,781
<i>Soviet ships have violated
the territorial waters--</i>

40
00:02:27,781 --> 00:02:30,509
[NAT KING COLE'S " UNFORGETTABLE"
PLAYS ON TV]

41
00:03:04,585 --> 00:03:06,849
Just a matter of time, I suppose.

42
00:03:26,474 --> 00:03:28,237
[GRUNTING]

43
00:04:32,206 --> 00:04:33,696
[YELLS]

44
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:37,073
[CHUCKLES]

45
00:04:37,478 --> 00:04:41,141
It's a joke. It's all a joke.

46
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:44,046
Mother, forgive me.

47
00:08:39,253 --> 00:08:42,279
[ARGUING INDISTINCTLY]

48
00:08:44,825 --> 00:08:47,794
SALLY:
I was a hero, goddamn it!

49
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:53,360
<i>MAN [ON TV] : --an act clearly meant to send
a signal to the government in Saigon...</i>

50
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:57,868
<i>...that violence and oppression
is not the way to peace.</i>

51
00:09:35,209 --> 00:09:37,700
MAN 1 :
Fuck you, pigs!

52
00:10:07,841 --> 00:10:10,969
MAN 2:
Good luck, Mr. Gorsky.

53
00:10:56,857 --> 00:10:59,917
MAN:
Get out of here, vigilantes!

54
00:10:59,917 --> 00:11:03,495
[CHATTERING]

55
00:11:07,635 --> 00:11:08,385
No!

56
00:11:33,827 --> 00:11:35,852
[SIRENS WAILING]

57
00:11:36,764 --> 00:11:42,896
GALLAGHER: Edward Blake. Sixty-seven
years old. Six-two, a solid 225.

58
00:11:43,404 --> 00:11:45,269
Guy was built like a linebacker.

59
00:11:45,269 --> 00:11:47,339
FINE:
Yeah, I saw the body.

60
00:11:47,339 --> 00:11:49,567
For a guy his age,
he was in terrific shape.

61
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:52,405
GALLAGHER:
You mean apart from being dead?

62
00:11:53,647 --> 00:11:55,137
That's plate glass.

63
00:11:55,137 --> 00:11:58,217
You'd have to step on the gas
just to put a crack in it.

64
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,444
Had to have been thrown.

65
00:12:00,444 --> 00:12:01,815
Check the bedroom?

66
00:12:01,815 --> 00:12:04,924
Yeah. Drawers opened, tossed through.

67
00:12:04,924 --> 00:12:08,152
Mattress flipped. Probably robbery.

68
00:12:08,152 --> 00:12:09,796
Or made to look like one.

69
00:12:09,796 --> 00:12:11,726
See this?

70
00:12:12,032 --> 00:12:15,263
-Shaking hands with the president.
FINE: Whoa.

71
00:12:15,263 --> 00:12:17,666
Think Blake was a spook?

72
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:21,501
Government or black ops?

73
00:12:21,809 --> 00:12:23,709
GALLAGHER:
I think...

74
00:12:24,011 --> 00:12:27,310
...this is way bigger than both of us.

75
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:35,719
<i>RORSCHACH:
Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.</i>

76
00:12:35,719 --> 00:12:40,986
<i>Dog carcass in alley this morning.
Tire tread on burst stomach.</i>

77
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:43,491
<i>This city's afraid of me.</i>

78
00:12:43,491 --> 00:12:47,600
<i>I've seen its true face.
The streets are extended gutters...</i>

79
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:50,668
<i>...and the gutters are full of blood.</i>

80
00:12:50,668 --> 00:12:53,306
<i>And when the drains finally scab over...</i>

81
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:56,605
<i>...all the vermin will drown.</i>

82
00:12:57,244 --> 00:12:59,644
<i>The accumulated filth of all their sex
and murder...</i>

83
00:12:59,644 --> 00:13:02,111
<i>...will foam up around their waists...</i>

84
00:13:02,111 --> 00:13:07,743
<i>...and all the whores and politicians
will look up and shout, " Save us. "</i>

85
00:13:08,722 --> 00:13:12,351
<i>And I'll whisper, "No. "</i>

86
00:13:13,861 --> 00:13:16,728
<i>Now the whole world
stands on the brink...</i>

87
00:13:16,728 --> 00:13:19,388
<i>...staring down into bloody hell.</i>

88
00:13:19,388 --> 00:13:23,093
<i>All those liberals and intellectuals...</i>

89
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:25,261
<i>...and smooth talkers...</i>

90
00:13:25,261 --> 00:13:28,897
<i>...and all of a sudden,
nobody can think of anything to say.</i>

91
00:13:28,897 --> 00:13:32,239
<i>Beneath me, this awful city.</i>

92
00:13:32,239 --> 00:13:36,179
<i>It screams like an abattoir
full of retarded children...</i>

93
00:13:36,179 --> 00:13:40,980
<i>...and the night reeks of fornication
and bad consciences.</i>

94
00:14:52,092 --> 00:14:53,092
Huh.

95
00:15:01,568 --> 00:15:05,698
<i>Tonight, a comedian died in New York.</i>

96
00:15:05,698 --> 00:15:07,238
<i>Somebody knows why.</i>

97
00:15:08,175 --> 00:15:10,439
Somebody knows.

98
00:15:11,178 --> 00:15:17,413
MAN: It all started with the gangs.
You know, people tend to forget that.

99
00:15:18,085 --> 00:15:21,179
Pirate outfits, ghosts.

100
00:15:21,179 --> 00:15:23,949
They thought it was funny:
dress up and pull heists.

101
00:15:23,949 --> 00:15:25,489
[MAN CHUCKLES]

102
00:15:25,489 --> 00:15:28,355
As soon as we'd arrest them,
they'd be back on the street.

103
00:15:28,355 --> 00:15:32,363
Nobody could pick them out of a lineup
because of the damn masks.

104
00:15:32,363 --> 00:15:34,797
So a few of us cops, we get together...

105
00:15:34,797 --> 00:15:38,335
...and we figure, what the heck,
we'll mask up, too.

106
00:15:38,335 --> 00:15:41,201
We'll finish what the law couldn’t.

107
00:15:42,009 --> 00:15:46,036
Pretty soon, the papers get wind of it.
They ran with it...

108
00:15:46,036 --> 00:15:49,876
...and oh, boy, we're a national pastime.

109
00:15:49,876 --> 00:15:53,542
It was me, Dollar Bill, Mothman...

110
00:15:53,542 --> 00:15:57,087
...Captain Metropolis, Hooded Justice...

111
00:15:57,087 --> 00:16:00,454
...Silk Spectre and the Comedian.

112
00:16:00,454 --> 00:16:04,154
Oh, don't get me started on him.

113
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:10,361
I must be drunk already,
telling you this sob story again.

114
00:16:10,361 --> 00:16:12,402
I think you were trying to make a point.

115
00:16:13,307 --> 00:16:19,473
Well, my point is that we had it too easy.
It wasn't fair what happened to you guys--

116
00:16:19,473 --> 00:16:23,776
You guys who picked up where we left off.
--with Nixon forcing you out.

117
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:29,278
Nixon, oh, that prick. To think I voted
for that prick five times.

118
00:16:29,278 --> 00:16:32,186
Hey, it was him or the commies, right?

119
00:16:34,995 --> 00:16:38,795
Oh, wow, it's almost midnight.
Gotta go.

120
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:41,961
Truth?

121
00:16:42,636 --> 00:16:46,367
You were a better Nite Owl
than I ever was, Danny boy.

122
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:50,271
-Hollis, we both know that's bullshit.
-Hey.

123
00:16:50,271 --> 00:16:51,706
Watch it with the language.

124
00:16:51,706 --> 00:16:54,506
This is the left hook
that floored Captain Axis, remember?

125
00:16:54,506 --> 00:16:55,705
Yeah.

126
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:58,443
DAN: Next week?
HOLLIS: Well...

127
00:16:58,443 --> 00:17:03,215
...you know, you don't have to
keep humoring me like this.

128
00:17:03,215 --> 00:17:05,551
If you got a hot date or something....

129
00:17:05,551 --> 00:17:08,524
Hey, us retired guys
have to stick together, right?

130
00:17:10,297 --> 00:17:12,162
You ever miss it?

131
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:15,460
No. You?

132
00:17:16,036 --> 00:17:17,833
Oh, heck, no.

133
00:17:19,139 --> 00:17:20,902
Be seeing you.

134
00:18:10,924 --> 00:18:13,791
[METAL SCRAPING]

135
00:18:21,902 --> 00:18:23,199
Hello, Daniel.

136
00:18:23,937 --> 00:18:25,029
Rorschach.

137
00:18:26,106 --> 00:18:30,406
Helped myself to some beans.
Hope you don't mind.

138
00:18:30,406 --> 00:18:33,011
No, no. Course not.

139
00:18:34,614 --> 00:18:37,174
You want me to heat those up for you?

140
00:18:37,174 --> 00:18:38,874
Fine like this.

141
00:18:40,454 --> 00:18:41,648
How have you been keeping?

142
00:18:46,026 --> 00:18:47,823
RORSCHACH:
Out of prison.

143
00:18:48,295 --> 00:18:49,785
So far.

144
00:18:50,764 --> 00:18:51,924
Daniel...

145
00:18:52,566 --> 00:18:54,056
...look at this.

146
00:19:01,308 --> 00:19:03,936
DAN: Is this bean juice?
RORSCHACH: Human bean juice.

147
00:19:04,644 --> 00:19:09,138
Badge belonged to the Comedian.
Blood too. He's dead.

148
00:19:11,151 --> 00:19:12,618
Let's talk downstairs.

149
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:15,183
It could have been a burglary.

150
00:19:15,183 --> 00:19:18,051
Maybe the killer didn't know
who the Comedian was.

151
00:19:18,051 --> 00:19:22,958
RORSCHACH: An ordinary burglar?
Kill the Comedian? Ridiculous.

152
00:19:24,531 --> 00:19:27,967
I heard he'd been working
for the government since '77...

153
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:31,298
...knocking over Marxist republics
in South America.

154
00:19:31,298 --> 00:19:34,406
Maybe it was a political killing
or something.

155
00:19:34,406 --> 00:19:35,836
Maybe.

156
00:19:35,836 --> 00:19:39,274
Maybe someone's picking off
costumed heroes.

157
00:19:39,274 --> 00:19:41,539
DAN:
You don't think that's a little paranoid?

158
00:19:41,539 --> 00:19:44,275
That what they say about me now?

159
00:19:44,518 --> 00:19:45,780
Paranoid?

160
00:19:45,780 --> 00:19:48,785
DAN: Look, Comedian made
a lot of enemies over the years...

161
00:19:48,785 --> 00:19:50,445
...even among his friends.

162
00:19:50,445 --> 00:19:52,785
RORSCHACH:
Speaking of friends, how's Hollis Mason?

163
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:57,619
He wrote that book. Said some bad things
about the Comedian in it.

164
00:19:57,619 --> 00:20:01,859
I don't like what you're implying,
and I like being followed even less.

165
00:20:02,402 --> 00:20:06,862
Maybe I was keeping an eye on you,
in case someone's gunning for masks.

166
00:20:06,862 --> 00:20:11,704
-You were never that sentimental.
-Attack on one is attack on all of us.

167
00:20:12,145 --> 00:20:14,579
What do you suggest we do about it?

168
00:20:15,482 --> 00:20:16,642
Retribution.

169
00:20:18,051 --> 00:20:21,350
-Watchmen are over.
-Says Tricky Dick.

170
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:23,284
Says me.

171
00:20:25,892 --> 00:20:27,519
Nobody knows who you are.

172
00:20:27,519 --> 00:20:30,663
You can give it up,
try and have a normal life.

173
00:20:30,663 --> 00:20:34,733
That what you have now?
A normal life?

174
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:39,102
When you walk down the street
in a city dying of rabies...

175
00:20:39,102 --> 00:20:40,739
...past the human cockroaches...

176
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:43,671
...talking about their heroin
and child pornography...

177
00:20:43,671 --> 00:20:45,368
...do you really feel normal?

178
00:20:46,513 --> 00:20:49,277
Least I'm not the one
still hiding behind a mask.

179
00:20:51,151 --> 00:20:52,413
No.

180
00:20:54,087 --> 00:20:56,214
You're hiding in plain sight.

181
00:20:57,591 --> 00:20:59,752
Be seeing you, Dan.

182
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:02,728
A maintenance hatch
will let you out two blocks north.

183
00:21:02,728 --> 00:21:04,625
Yeah, I remember.

184
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:08,859
Came here often,
when we were partners.

185
00:21:08,859 --> 00:21:10,935
DAN: Those were great times, huh,
Rorschach?

186
00:21:11,438 --> 00:21:14,669
-What happened?
-You quit.

187
00:21:41,902 --> 00:21:42,926
<i>MAN:
Mr. Veidt...</i>

188
00:21:43,703 --> 00:21:45,864
...to date,
you're one of only two Watchmen...

189
00:21:45,864 --> 00:21:48,473
...ever to reveal their true identity
to the world...

190
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:50,576
...the first being Hollis Mason.

191
00:21:50,576 --> 00:21:53,736
And you've certainly profited greatly
by it...

192
00:21:53,736 --> 00:21:59,181
...turning your superhero alter ego,
Ozymandias, into a billion-dollar industry:

193
00:21:59,181 --> 00:22:02,412
Toys, lunchboxes, genetic engineering.

194
00:22:02,412 --> 00:22:04,648
I understand there's a movie
in the works.

195
00:22:04,648 --> 00:22:09,022
-I'm not hearing a question, Mr. Roth.
ROTH: I'm sorry. Do you think--

196
00:22:09,022 --> 00:22:11,755
The Watchmen resent me
for prostituting their struggle?

197
00:22:11,755 --> 00:22:14,662
It's a fair question.
Yes, it's crossed my mind...

198
00:22:14,662 --> 00:22:17,860
...some of my old colleagues
might see it that way...

199
00:22:17,860 --> 00:22:21,030
...just as you're clearly aware
that biased journalism...

200
00:22:21,030 --> 00:22:23,801
...sells more magazines.

201
00:22:24,311 --> 00:22:29,078
The merchandising arm of Veidt Industries
is funding our work with Dr. Manhattan.

202
00:22:29,078 --> 00:22:32,184
We recently expanded our research facility
in Antarctica...

203
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:35,583
...in the hope of developing cheap,
renewable sources of energy...

204
00:22:35,583 --> 00:22:38,747
...that we might eliminate
the world’s reliance on fossil fuels.

205
00:22:38,747 --> 00:22:41,359
Now, it doesn't take
a political scientist...

206
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:44,929
...to see that our Cold War
with the Russians isn't ideological...

207
00:22:44,929 --> 00:22:48,590
...it's based upon fear.
Fear of not having enough.

208
00:22:48,969 --> 00:22:52,666
But if we make resources infinite...

209
00:22:52,666 --> 00:22:54,932
...ah...

210
00:22:54,932 --> 00:22:57,201
...we make war obsolete.

211
00:22:58,044 --> 00:23:01,878
I would hope the other Watchmen
understand that...

212
00:23:03,083 --> 00:23:04,744
...wherever they may be.

213
00:23:06,853 --> 00:23:08,218
Thanks for your time.

214
00:23:14,461 --> 00:23:17,123
-You look good, Adrian.
-Dan.

215
00:23:17,123 --> 00:23:19,527
It's been too long.

216
00:23:21,267 --> 00:23:25,328
So Rorschach thinks
someone's hunting the Watchmen, huh?

217
00:23:26,006 --> 00:23:27,871
You think it's possible?

218
00:23:27,871 --> 00:23:30,771
Statistically, one murder
doesn't equal a trend.

219
00:23:31,911 --> 00:23:33,879
Rorschach's a sociopath, Dan.

220
00:23:34,514 --> 00:23:37,881
And so was the Comedian.
He was practically a Nazi.

221
00:23:38,718 --> 00:23:40,743
You know that better than anyone.

222
00:23:40,743 --> 00:23:43,115
I'm not here because I miss him.

223
00:23:43,115 --> 00:23:44,620
It's obviously occurred to Rorschach...

224
00:23:44,620 --> 00:23:47,760
...that we're the only ones
who know each other's identities.

225
00:23:48,261 --> 00:23:50,354
Actually, the whole world knows yours.

226
00:23:51,131 --> 00:23:53,599
That's why I'm warning you first.

227
00:23:57,203 --> 00:23:59,194
Thank you, Dan...

228
00:24:00,807 --> 00:24:04,607
...but I fear there's something
much more real to worry about...

229
00:24:04,607 --> 00:24:07,372
...than Rorschach's mask killer.

230
00:24:08,882 --> 00:24:13,410
If the Russians do launch their nukes,
can Jon really stop them?

231
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:17,215
The Soviets have 51,000
warheads stockpiled.

232
00:24:17,215 --> 00:24:20,587
Even if Jon stops 99 percent of them...

233
00:24:20,587 --> 00:24:24,958
...the 1 percent that get through
could still kill every living thing on Earth.

234
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:30,066
Even Dr. Manhattan
can't be everywhere at once.

235
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:49,949
<i>Rorschach's journal,
October 13th, 1985...</i>

236
00:24:49,949 --> 00:24:52,455
<i>...8:30 p.m.</i>

237
00:24:53,159 --> 00:24:57,061
<i>Meeting with Dreiberg
left bad taste in mouth.</i>

238
00:24:57,263 --> 00:25:01,324
<i>A flabby failure who sits
whimpering in his basement.</i>

239
00:25:02,502 --> 00:25:05,471
<i>Why are so few of us left active...</i>

240
00:25:05,471 --> 00:25:10,507
<i>...healthy and without
personality disorders?</i>

241
00:25:10,507 --> 00:25:13,908
<i>The first Nite Owl
runs an auto-repair shop.</i>

242
00:25:13,908 --> 00:25:17,481
<i>The first Silk Spectre
is a bloated, aging whore...</i>

243
00:25:17,481 --> 00:25:20,517
<i>...dying in a California rest resort.</i>

244
00:25:20,517 --> 00:25:23,281
<i>Dollar Bill got his cape stuck
in a revolving door...</i>

245
00:25:23,281 --> 00:25:24,980
<i>...where he got gunned down.</i>

246
00:25:25,592 --> 00:25:28,026
<i>Silhouette, murdered...</i>

247
00:25:28,361 --> 00:25:31,296
<i>...a victim of her own indecent lifestyle.</i>

248
00:25:31,865 --> 00:25:34,857
<i>Mothman's in an asylum in Maine.</i>

249
00:25:38,872 --> 00:25:42,000
<i>Only two names remain on my list.</i>

250
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:47,272
<i>Both share private quarters
at Rockefeller Military Research Center.</i>

251
00:25:47,272 --> 00:25:49,779
<i>I shall go to them.</i>

252
00:25:50,116 --> 00:25:55,554
<i>I shall go tell the indestructible man
that someone plans to murder him.</i>

253
00:26:03,329 --> 00:26:05,126
JON:
Good evening, Rorschach.

254
00:26:05,126 --> 00:26:08,790
RORSCHACH:
Dr. Manhattan, you know why I'm here.

255
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:10,401
JON:
Yes...

256
00:26:11,671 --> 00:26:13,639
...but you're going to leave disappointed.

257
00:26:13,639 --> 00:26:17,537
Rorschach. You shouldn’t be here.
You're a wanted man.

258
00:26:17,537 --> 00:26:19,905
RORSCHACH:
Nice to see you too, Silk Spectre.

259
00:26:19,905 --> 00:26:22,138
I have a real name I've been using
a couple years.

260
00:26:22,138 --> 00:26:23,339
Now, Try it.

261
00:26:23,339 --> 00:26:25,609
Whatever you say, Laurie.

262
00:26:25,609 --> 00:26:27,013
What are you doing here?

263
00:26:27,013 --> 00:26:29,519
JON:
The Comedian is dead.

264
00:26:29,519 --> 00:26:31,782
Rorschach wants me
to look into my future...

265
00:26:32,125 --> 00:26:34,593
...see if the killer is ever
publicly identified.

266
00:26:34,593 --> 00:26:37,855
Already warned Dreiberg.
Came to warn you too.

267
00:26:40,567 --> 00:26:42,933
Even if I wanted to help...

268
00:26:43,536 --> 00:26:47,438
...my future is blocked
by some kind of temporal interference.

269
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:51,901
-I cannot see it clearly.
-Interference? Caused by what?

270
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:55,479
In all likelihood, nuclear holocaust.

271
00:26:56,216 --> 00:27:00,312
If the United States and Soviet Union
engage in all-out war...

272
00:27:00,312 --> 00:27:04,479
...the resulting blast wave would produce
a sudden burst of tachyons...

273
00:27:04,479 --> 00:27:09,617
...particles which travel backward
through what you perceive as time...

274
00:27:10,263 --> 00:27:13,596
...therefore obscuring my vision
of the present.

275
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,799
I must return to my work.

276
00:27:15,799 --> 00:27:17,095
RORSCHACH:
Wait a minute.

277
00:27:17,095 --> 00:27:19,761
What if that's why
someone wants us out of the way?

278
00:27:19,761 --> 00:27:22,169
So we can't do anything to stop it?

279
00:27:22,169 --> 00:27:24,173
Goodbye, Rorschach.

280
00:27:24,173 --> 00:27:26,608
RORSCHACH: Took a lot of effort
to get in here to see you.

281
00:27:26,608 --> 00:27:28,110
I'm not leaving--

282
00:27:29,382 --> 00:27:31,714
--till I've had my say.

283
00:27:39,225 --> 00:27:42,160
Seems like there's a lot of things
you don't tell me these days.

284
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:45,024
I didn't wanna worry you prematurely.

285
00:27:45,498 --> 00:27:49,628
If Adrian and I can solve the energy crisis,
war may be averted.

286
00:27:49,628 --> 00:27:51,861
LAURIE:
But you always say time is simultaneous.

287
00:27:52,572 --> 00:27:55,439
If that's true,
then how can you change the future?

288
00:27:55,439 --> 00:28:00,602
If only you could perceive time as I do.

289
00:28:00,602 --> 00:28:02,042
Please let me show you.

290
00:28:08,021 --> 00:28:12,958
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
I was a hero, goddamn it!

291
00:28:12,958 --> 00:28:16,186
It's not my fault you got old.
What do you have to complain about?

292
00:28:16,186 --> 00:28:18,796
I'm putting food on the table
for you and your child.

293
00:28:18,796 --> 00:28:21,729
Call your friend Eddie.
Maybe he can give you a better life.

294
00:28:21,729 --> 00:28:26,065
-It was a mistake. One time.
-Man tries to rape you--

295
00:28:26,372 --> 00:28:27,737
Stop!

296
00:28:28,508 --> 00:28:29,975
Your mind goes to dark places...

297
00:28:29,975 --> 00:28:32,475
...and you wonder
why I keep the worst from you.

298
00:28:36,416 --> 00:28:39,852
-Say hello to Dan for me.
-What?

299
00:28:41,621 --> 00:28:44,419
You wanna ask me
to go to dinner with you...

300
00:28:46,125 --> 00:28:48,286
...like we used to...

301
00:28:49,729 --> 00:28:50,855
...but you won't.

302
00:28:51,631 --> 00:28:53,895
You know I can't.

303
00:28:56,536 --> 00:28:58,800
So you'll call Dan...

304
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:01,433
...which is only natural.

305
00:29:01,774 --> 00:29:04,368
You deserve the comfort of an old friend.

306
00:29:38,678 --> 00:29:40,202
LAURIE:
Dan Dreiberg's table.

307
00:30:01,367 --> 00:30:05,133
DAN: Did you know that
he and H.J. were--? I had no idea.

308
00:30:05,638 --> 00:30:08,698
You remember that crazy guy?
What'd he call himself?

309
00:30:08,698 --> 00:30:10,365
Captain Carnage.

310
00:30:10,365 --> 00:30:13,740
Used to pretend he was a supervillain
just so he could get beat up?

311
00:30:13,740 --> 00:30:16,313
Yeah, he tried that on me once.
I just walked away.

312
00:30:16,313 --> 00:30:19,508
He starts following me down the street
in broad daylight...

313
00:30:19,508 --> 00:30:22,483
...yelling, " Punish me! Punish me!"

314
00:30:22,722 --> 00:30:25,247
I'm just saying, " No, get lost."

315
00:30:26,392 --> 00:30:28,860
God, whatever happened to him?

316
00:30:28,860 --> 00:30:31,189
Oh. Um....
He pulled that on Rorschach...

317
00:30:31,189 --> 00:30:33,764
...and Rorschach
dropped him down an elevator shaft.

318
00:30:40,239 --> 00:30:42,639
Oh, my God. That's not even funny.

319
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:45,833
-It's a little funny.
-Yep.

320
00:30:47,747 --> 00:30:49,715
WOMAN: I'm glad I ordered
the four-legged chicken.

321
00:30:49,715 --> 00:30:51,850
It's really good to see you again.

322
00:30:53,085 --> 00:30:54,609
It's great seeing you too.

323
00:30:55,421 --> 00:30:57,946
Why'd we do it, Dan? Dress up like that?

324
00:30:59,091 --> 00:31:02,424
-No one else would.
-Yeah, but do you remember my costume?

325
00:31:02,424 --> 00:31:05,689
AII that tight latex?
I mean, it was awful.

326
00:31:05,689 --> 00:31:08,834
Uh.... Yeah, yeah, awful.

327
00:31:08,834 --> 00:31:11,435
But didn't wanna disappoint Mother.

328
00:31:11,435 --> 00:31:15,597
Wanted her little girl to be just like her
and fight bad guys.

329
00:31:16,275 --> 00:31:19,870
I think the Keene Act was the best thing
that ever happened to us.

330
00:31:20,947 --> 00:31:23,313
Well, we’ll live longer anyway.

331
00:31:26,619 --> 00:31:28,143
What?

332
00:31:29,121 --> 00:31:33,615
Jon thinks, unless he can do something
about it...

333
00:31:34,460 --> 00:31:36,485
...that there's gonna be nuclear war.

334
00:31:36,963 --> 00:31:38,453
Soon.

335
00:31:39,332 --> 00:31:42,665
But I don't know what to think.
I mean, it's all...

336
00:31:42,665 --> 00:31:45,895
...quantum mechanics
and parallel realities with him.

337
00:31:45,895 --> 00:31:48,836
I never even know
what universe he's actually seeing.

338
00:31:50,142 --> 00:31:53,270
He just keeps getting further away
from me.

339
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:55,641
Everyone.

340
00:31:56,749 --> 00:31:59,411
I can't even tell
if he actually cares about me anymore...

341
00:31:59,411 --> 00:32:01,610
...or if he's just pretending.

342
00:32:02,321 --> 00:32:05,256
If he's pretending, it means he cares.

343
00:32:09,996 --> 00:32:11,987
Hold on, I'II get the door.

344
00:32:13,332 --> 00:32:15,129
Thanks, Dan.

345
00:32:15,501 --> 00:32:17,526
-Got it?
-Yeah.

346
00:32:22,341 --> 00:32:23,569
I'm sorry.

347
00:32:23,569 --> 00:32:27,645
I invite you out to dinner to catch up
and have a few laughs...

348
00:32:28,014 --> 00:32:31,381
...but there don't seem to be many laughs
around these days.

349
00:32:31,381 --> 00:32:35,351
What do you expect?
The Comedian's dead.

350
00:34:03,275 --> 00:34:05,334
[VOMITING]

351
00:34:07,013 --> 00:34:10,574
Laurie? Is that you?

352
00:34:13,285 --> 00:34:16,254
Thought you'd be used
to traveling that way by now.

353
00:34:16,922 --> 00:34:20,915
Well, I'm not.
I hate it when Jon teleports me.

354
00:34:20,915 --> 00:34:23,960
Well, it beats flying coach.

355
00:34:24,330 --> 00:34:26,321
Margarita?

356
00:34:26,565 --> 00:34:28,726
Mother, it's 2:00 in the afternoon.

357
00:34:28,726 --> 00:34:30,869
[CHUCKLES]

358
00:34:31,437 --> 00:34:32,187
Mm.

359
00:34:33,572 --> 00:34:35,870
Remember that guy
that writes me letters?

360
00:34:36,242 --> 00:34:39,541
He sent me an item of memorabilia.
It's a Tijuana bible.

361
00:34:39,541 --> 00:34:43,876
This little eight-page porno comic
they did in the '30s and '40s.

362
00:34:43,876 --> 00:34:48,077
-He sent you this?
-Sure. They're very valuable, like antiques.

363
00:34:48,888 --> 00:34:50,583
Mother, this is gross.

364
00:34:50,583 --> 00:34:53,020
I think it's kind of flattering.

365
00:34:53,020 --> 00:34:55,456
Why do you always call me Mother
when you're mad?

366
00:34:56,829 --> 00:35:00,890
I know why you're here.
I can still read, you know.

367
00:35:01,667 --> 00:35:03,897
I saw it in the paper.

368
00:35:04,570 --> 00:35:07,471
Eddie Blake’s funeral is today.

369
00:35:09,275 --> 00:35:12,267
Finally got his punchline, I guess.

370
00:35:12,745 --> 00:35:15,578
-Poor Eddie.
-Poor Eddie? After what he did to you?

371
00:35:16,282 --> 00:35:17,806
Oh, Laurie, you're still young.

372
00:35:18,584 --> 00:35:20,518
You don't know.

373
00:35:20,518 --> 00:35:22,449
Things change.

374
00:35:23,289 --> 00:35:26,053
What happened happened 40 years ago.

375
00:35:26,053 --> 00:35:29,490
I'm 67 years old.

376
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:33,860
Every day, the future
looks a little bit darker.

377
00:35:34,700 --> 00:35:36,861
But the past...

378
00:35:37,369 --> 00:35:40,361
...even the grimy parts of it...

379
00:35:40,906 --> 00:35:43,534
...keep on getting brighter.

380
00:35:49,048 --> 00:35:51,881
I've got spots in my eyes.

381
00:35:53,619 --> 00:35:55,177
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

382
00:35:55,177 --> 00:35:58,016
Stop it, Eddie.

383
00:35:58,991 --> 00:36:02,358
-Thank you, Weegee.
-Thank you, Mr. Owl.

384
00:36:03,562 --> 00:36:06,759
Tomorrow, 3:00, my studio.

385
00:36:06,759 --> 00:36:10,095
-Little place on 21st.
-Sounds good.

386
00:36:10,095 --> 00:36:14,865
SALLY: Wow, a real photo session.
Wonder how my hair will look?

387
00:36:17,176 --> 00:36:20,373
Oh, go ahead. I'll be there in five.

388
00:36:36,862 --> 00:36:37,886
Eddie.

389
00:36:38,964 --> 00:36:43,025
What the hell are you doing here?
You knew I was changing.

390
00:36:43,025 --> 00:36:44,794
Sure I did.

391
00:36:46,438 --> 00:36:48,030
Come on, baby.

392
00:36:48,474 --> 00:36:50,465
I know what you need.

393
00:36:50,465 --> 00:36:54,704
You gotta have some kind of reason
for dressing in an outfit like this.

394
00:36:54,704 --> 00:36:57,178
I said no, Eddie.

395
00:36:57,817 --> 00:37:02,720
-No spelled Y-E-S.
-No spelled N-O.

396
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:06,324
-AII right?
-Come on, sweetheart.

397
00:37:10,262 --> 00:37:11,854
Eddie....

398
00:37:15,067 --> 00:37:16,932
[GRUNTING]

399
00:37:20,706 --> 00:37:22,697
[EDDIE LAUGHS]

400
00:37:49,702 --> 00:37:52,432
You little bastard.

401
00:37:59,044 --> 00:38:00,068
This what you like?

402
00:38:00,068 --> 00:38:02,737
-This what makes you hot?
-What?

403
00:38:13,225 --> 00:38:16,422
Things are tough all over, cupcake.

404
00:38:16,422 --> 00:38:20,691
It rains on the just and the unjust alike.

405
00:38:20,691 --> 00:38:24,700
The Comedian was a little bit of both.

406
00:38:26,171 --> 00:38:29,538
And he always thought
he'd get the last laugh.

407
00:38:30,075 --> 00:38:33,135
MAN: Thou knowest, Lord,
the secrets of our hearts.

408
00:38:33,746 --> 00:38:37,079
Shut not thy merciful ears
to our prayers...

409
00:38:37,079 --> 00:38:41,845
...but spare us, Lord most holy,
O God most mighty...

410
00:38:41,845 --> 00:38:45,081
...O holy and merciful savior.

411
00:38:45,758 --> 00:38:48,488
Thou most worthy judge eternal.

412
00:38:48,488 --> 00:38:51,994
Suffer us not at our last hour
for any--

413
00:39:49,588 --> 00:39:52,022
EDDIE:
Fireworks. You gotta be kidding me.

414
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:56,924
You know, you'd think this goddamn
country had had enough fireworks.

415
00:39:57,830 --> 00:40:00,424
You know, if we'd lost here in Vietnam...

416
00:40:00,424 --> 00:40:05,559
...I think it might have driven us crazy.
You know, as a country.

417
00:40:06,338 --> 00:40:10,035
But we didn't, thanks to you.

418
00:40:12,011 --> 00:40:13,945
You sound bitter.

419
00:40:13,945 --> 00:40:15,774
Me? Bitter?

420
00:40:15,774 --> 00:40:19,008
Fuck, no. I think it's hilarious.

421
00:40:20,853 --> 00:40:23,947
[JANIS JOPLIN'S " ME AND BOBBY McGEE"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

422
00:40:25,357 --> 00:40:27,188
Oh, Jesus Christ.

423
00:40:27,188 --> 00:40:30,351
-Mr. Eddie?
-Just what I fucking needed.

424
00:40:30,351 --> 00:40:35,592
The war is over now.
We must talk about this baby.

425
00:40:36,368 --> 00:40:39,895
There's nothing to talk about.
See, I'm leaving.

426
00:40:39,895 --> 00:40:41,403
I'm gonna forget about you...

427
00:40:41,403 --> 00:40:44,406
...and your horrible, sweaty,
little piece-of-shit country.

428
00:40:44,977 --> 00:40:46,137
Get the fuck out of here.

429
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:49,745
-No.
-Get the fuck out of here.

430
00:40:49,745 --> 00:40:51,280
You will remember.

431
00:40:53,052 --> 00:40:55,782
You will remember me and my country...

432
00:40:56,655 --> 00:40:58,282
...forever!

433
00:41:00,893 --> 00:41:02,758
My face!

434
00:41:04,963 --> 00:41:06,123
Blake. Don't.

435
00:41:06,932 --> 00:41:08,229
Blake!

436
00:41:15,107 --> 00:41:17,598
She was pregnant...

437
00:41:18,877 --> 00:41:20,606
...and you gunned her down.

438
00:41:20,606 --> 00:41:22,041
That's right...

439
00:41:22,041 --> 00:41:24,148
...and you know what? You watched me.

440
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:27,308
You could have turned the gun to steam,
the bullets to mercury...

441
00:41:27,308 --> 00:41:31,081
...the bottle into goddamn snowflakes,
but you didn't, did you?

442
00:41:33,025 --> 00:41:35,858
You really don't give a damn
about human beings.

443
00:41:37,029 --> 00:41:39,862
You're drifting out of touch, Doc.

444
00:41:41,433 --> 00:41:43,628
God help us all.

445
00:41:45,637 --> 00:41:46,934
Medic!

446
00:41:53,779 --> 00:41:56,942
<i>MAN:
Most holy and merciful savior.</i>

447
00:41:57,883 --> 00:42:02,115
He cometh up and is cut down,
like a flower.

448
00:42:02,955 --> 00:42:07,153
In the midst of life, we are in death.

449
00:42:09,461 --> 00:42:13,090
ADRIAN: Welcome to the first meeting--
-This is bullshit.

450
00:42:13,090 --> 00:42:17,634
For a guy who calls himself the Comedian,
I can never tell when you're joking.

451
00:42:17,634 --> 00:42:21,204
Watchmen. That's the real joke.

452
00:42:21,204 --> 00:42:24,171
It didn't work 15 years ago,
and it ain't gonna work now...

453
00:42:24,171 --> 00:42:26,470
...because you wanna play
cowboys and Indians.

454
00:42:26,470 --> 00:42:29,011
Maybe we should agree
on no drinking at meetings.

455
00:42:29,011 --> 00:42:30,648
[LAUGHS]

456
00:42:30,648 --> 00:42:34,547
Rorschach and I have made headway
on the gang problem by working together.

457
00:42:34,547 --> 00:42:39,054
A group this size seems like
a publicity stunt. I'm not in it for the ink.

458
00:42:39,054 --> 00:42:41,021
ADRIAN:
We can do so much more.

459
00:42:41,021 --> 00:42:43,388
We can save this world...

460
00:42:43,388 --> 00:42:44,824
[EDDIE CHUCKLES]

461
00:42:44,824 --> 00:42:48,160
-...with the right leadership.
-Yeah.

462
00:42:50,502 --> 00:42:52,265
And that'd be you, right, Ozzy?

463
00:42:52,265 --> 00:42:55,201
I mean, hell,
you're the smartest man on the planet.

464
00:42:55,201 --> 00:42:58,036
It doesn't take a genius
to see the world has problems.

465
00:42:58,410 --> 00:43:02,073
But it takes a room of morons to think
they're small enough for you to handle.

466
00:43:03,048 --> 00:43:06,984
You know, mankind's been trying to kill
each other off since the beginning of time.

467
00:43:06,984 --> 00:43:11,987
Now we finally have the power
to finish the job.

468
00:43:12,224 --> 00:43:15,853
Ain't nothing gonna matter once
those nukes start flying. We’ll all be dust.

469
00:43:18,997 --> 00:43:21,022
Then Ozymandias here...

470
00:43:22,034 --> 00:43:24,298
...will be the smartest man
on the cinder.

471
00:43:33,212 --> 00:43:35,271
<i>MAN:
For as much as it hath pleased...</i>

472
00:43:35,547 --> 00:43:40,416
...almighty God to take onto himself
the soul of our dear departed brother...

473
00:43:41,820 --> 00:43:45,881
...let us therefore commit his body
to the ground.

474
00:43:45,881 --> 00:43:49,516
Earth to earth, ashes to ashes....

475
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:54,724
[CHATTERING]

476
00:43:54,724 --> 00:43:56,697
[GRUNTS]

477
00:44:08,814 --> 00:44:15,083
Watchmen! Police!
Police to protect the people!

478
00:44:19,625 --> 00:44:23,652
DAN: Attention, citizens.
