01:44:24,382 --> 01:44:26,518
World War III could start tomorrow.

1194
01:44:28,621 --> 01:44:29,952
Right?

1195
01:44:31,624 --> 01:44:32,955
Right.

1196
01:46:20,633 --> 01:46:23,363
[EKG FLATLINING]

1197
01:46:24,036 --> 01:46:26,869
[ALARM WAILING]

1198
01:46:26,869 --> 01:46:28,267
[MEN YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

1199
01:46:28,267 --> 01:46:29,703
[SCREAMS]

1200
01:46:29,703 --> 01:46:31,570
[THUDS]

1201
01:46:33,612 --> 01:46:36,137
[SCREAMING]

1202
01:46:39,585 --> 01:46:41,485
MAN:
Come back here!

1203
01:46:44,090 --> 01:46:45,785
He's dead, Rorschach.

1204
01:46:45,785 --> 01:46:50,156
While everyone's distracted, we thought
we'd bring you a little housewarming gift.

1205
01:46:50,156 --> 01:46:52,490
Something from the machine shop.

1206
01:46:54,100 --> 01:46:55,727
Hey, boss, you notice?

1207
01:46:55,727 --> 01:46:58,927
None of that " small world,
tall order" crap.

1208
01:46:58,927 --> 01:47:02,336
He knows once we slice open his lock,
he's next on the block.

1209
01:47:02,775 --> 01:47:03,901
Fat chance.

1210
01:47:04,610 --> 01:47:05,736
You're dead, Rorschach!

1211
01:47:05,736 --> 01:47:09,574
We got a prison full of killers out here.
What do you got?

1212
01:47:11,183 --> 01:47:12,343
[SCREAMING]

1213
01:47:12,343 --> 01:47:14,952
Your hands, my pleasure.

1214
01:47:14,952 --> 01:47:16,349
[CRACKING]

1215
01:47:16,656 --> 01:47:18,947
LLOYD:
I Can't reach the lock. Should I cut the bars?

1216
01:47:18,947 --> 01:47:22,424
This riot won't last.
I been waiting 15 years for this.

1217
01:47:23,562 --> 01:47:26,929
I'm sorry, Lawrence, but you're in the way
of my revenge.

1218
01:47:30,636 --> 01:47:32,365
Nothing personal, big guy.

1219
01:47:32,365 --> 01:47:33,630
[SAW BUZZING]

1220
01:47:33,630 --> 01:47:35,797
Boss! Wait!

1221
01:47:49,088 --> 01:47:50,885
Now you find out what the score is.

1222
01:47:51,323 --> 01:47:54,451
One-nothing. Come and get me.

1223
01:48:00,499 --> 01:48:02,160
Come on.

1224
01:48:02,160 --> 01:48:03,961
<i>DAN:
So I've been thinking.</i>

1225
01:48:04,837 --> 01:48:09,001
I feel that we have an obligation
to our fraternity.

1226
01:48:09,842 --> 01:48:12,902
-I think we ought to spring Rorschach.
LAURIE: What?

1227
01:48:12,902 --> 01:48:14,841
DAN:
Someone set him up.

1228
01:48:15,681 --> 01:48:19,276
And this whole cancer thing with Jon,
it just doesn't make sense.

1229
01:48:19,276 --> 01:48:21,385
You didn't get it.

1230
01:48:21,687 --> 01:48:24,121
Yeah, but breaking
into a maximum-security prison...

1231
01:48:24,121 --> 01:48:27,953
-...is a little different than putting out a fire.
-Yeah, you're right.

1232
01:48:28,861 --> 01:48:30,692
It'll be more fun.

1233
01:48:34,867 --> 01:48:37,859
Hurry, Lloyd. I wanna
smell this son of a bitch cooking.

1234
01:48:43,142 --> 01:48:44,871
Yes.

1235
01:48:49,615 --> 01:48:50,639
No.

1236
01:49:04,563 --> 01:49:09,398
Never disposed of sewage
with a toilet before. Obvious, really.

1237
01:49:10,236 --> 01:49:13,535
Two-nothing. Your move.

1238
01:49:16,542 --> 01:49:17,999
BIG FIGURE:
Get out of the way! Move it!

1239
01:49:51,254 --> 01:49:52,812
No. No.

1240
01:49:53,456 --> 01:49:54,855
Where's my face?

1241
01:49:57,393 --> 01:49:59,122
Don't kill me.

1242
01:50:02,799 --> 01:50:04,198
Your turn, doctor.

1243
01:50:04,198 --> 01:50:07,564
Tell me, what do you see?

1244
01:51:33,723 --> 01:51:35,452
Don't move!

1245
01:51:43,733 --> 01:51:45,496
Rorschach.

1246
01:51:46,002 --> 01:51:48,800
Daniel. Miss Jupiter.

1247
01:51:48,800 --> 01:51:52,372
Excuse me. Have to visit men's room.

1248
01:51:52,909 --> 01:51:54,877
Oh, for chrissake.

1249
01:52:09,325 --> 01:52:11,816
[TOILET FLUSHES]

1250
01:52:55,705 --> 01:52:57,832
Are you all right?

1251
01:52:59,275 --> 01:53:01,470
Yeah. Just...

1252
01:53:01,911 --> 01:53:03,173
...heavy, you know?

1253
01:53:03,980 --> 01:53:06,073
War, jailbreak.

1254
01:53:06,616 --> 01:53:11,485
Don't worry about it. Okay?
Everything's gonna be fine.

1255
01:53:16,492 --> 01:53:19,518
-Hello, Laurie.
-Jon.

1256
01:53:19,518 --> 01:53:23,324
-TV said you were on Mars.
-I am on Mars.

1257
01:53:23,900 --> 01:53:26,300
You and I are about
to have a conversation there.

1258
01:53:26,300 --> 01:53:27,936
What are you talking about?

1259
01:53:27,936 --> 01:53:30,766
You're going to try to convince me
to save the world.

1260
01:53:36,679 --> 01:53:39,671
-Laurie, don't.
-Dan, trust me.

1261
01:53:39,671 --> 01:53:41,510
I have to go.

1262
01:53:47,189 --> 01:53:49,180
Beautiful, isn't it?

1263
01:53:49,180 --> 01:53:51,292
[GAGGING]

1264
01:53:52,528 --> 01:53:53,859
[BREATHES]

1265
01:53:53,859 --> 01:53:56,965
Forgive me. These things sometimes
slip my mind.

1266
01:53:58,367 --> 01:54:00,198
It won't happen again.

1267
01:54:01,871 --> 01:54:03,862
LAURIE:
That's comforting.

1268
01:54:06,208 --> 01:54:07,869
Oh, my God.

1269
01:54:08,544 --> 01:54:10,375
I'm on Mars.

1270
01:54:11,881 --> 01:54:16,215
RORSCHACH: We need to hit up
underworld contacts, squeeze people.

1271
01:54:16,215 --> 01:54:19,115
Sure, why don't we just pick names
out of a phone book?

1272
01:54:19,115 --> 01:54:21,415
You forgot how we do things, Daniel.

1273
01:54:21,415 --> 01:54:26,050
You've gone too soft. Too trusting.
Especially with women.

1274
01:54:26,050 --> 01:54:28,321
Okay, no. Listen, I've had it with that.

1275
01:54:28,321 --> 01:54:30,522
God, who do you
think you are, Rorschach?

1276
01:54:30,522 --> 01:54:32,793
You live off people
while insulting them...

1277
01:54:32,793 --> 01:54:36,769
...and no one complains because they think
you're a goddamn lunatic.

1278
01:54:48,751 --> 01:54:50,582
I'm sorry.

1279
01:54:53,255 --> 01:54:55,416
I shouldn’t have said that, man.

1280
01:54:57,426 --> 01:54:58,757
Daniel...

1281
01:55:00,262 --> 01:55:02,730
...you are a good friend.

1282
01:55:05,601 --> 01:55:08,764
I know it can be difficult
with me sometimes.

1283
01:55:15,277 --> 01:55:16,767
Forget it.

1284
01:55:17,947 --> 01:55:19,608
It's okay, man.

1285
01:55:20,883 --> 01:55:22,475
Let's do it your way.

1286
01:55:33,729 --> 01:55:36,823
[WAYLON JENNINGS' " CLYDE"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

1287
01:55:41,537 --> 01:55:42,834
Oh, God.

1288
01:55:42,834 --> 01:55:47,374
Pyramid Transnational.
Anyone heard of it?

1289
01:55:54,850 --> 01:55:56,340
Oh, you bastards.

1290
01:55:56,340 --> 01:55:59,613
I buy everyone a round
and you sell me out like this?

1291
01:56:00,823 --> 01:56:04,122
Back off, or I'II stick this glass
in your squidgy face.

1292
01:56:04,122 --> 01:56:05,658
[GRUNTS]

1293
01:56:05,658 --> 01:56:08,763
Everybody stay calm.
We'll try to keep this brief.

1294
01:56:08,763 --> 01:56:11,229
Roy Chess. On Pyramid payroll.

1295
01:56:11,229 --> 01:56:15,894
Tried to kill Adrian Veidt. Dead now.
Did you know him?

1296
01:56:15,894 --> 01:56:16,644
No.

1297
01:56:17,940 --> 01:56:18,929
[MAN GROANING]

1298
01:56:18,929 --> 01:56:20,370
Yeah, yeah!

1299
01:56:20,370 --> 01:56:23,478
-I hired him. I knew him from the inside.
-You're a felon.

1300
01:56:23,478 --> 01:56:26,615
I was. I've been straight
ever since I got out, I swear.

1301
01:56:26,615 --> 01:56:30,513
I barely knew Chess that well,
but I was told to hire from the old life.

1302
01:56:30,513 --> 01:56:34,281
-Told by whom?
-My contact, Miss Slater.

1303
01:56:34,281 --> 01:56:37,051
Janey Slater works for Pyramid too?

1304
01:56:37,051 --> 01:56:41,185
Yeah, she was real nice. She said hiring
ex-cons was part of the company program.

1305
01:56:41,185 --> 01:56:45,060
Give people a second chance.
God, please let go! I'm telling the truth!

1306
01:56:49,205 --> 01:56:52,436
Janey Slater, Manhattan's old girlfriend.

1307
01:56:52,436 --> 01:56:55,304
Adrian's people might help us
find out who's underwriting Pyramid.

1308
01:56:55,304 --> 01:56:56,911
Follow the money.

1309
01:56:59,381 --> 01:57:02,544
JON:
This is where we hold our conversation.

1310
01:57:03,285 --> 01:57:08,348
In it, you ask me
to stop the imminent nuclear war.

1311
01:57:08,891 --> 01:57:11,553
But why would I save a world...

1312
01:57:11,553 --> 01:57:13,991
...I no longer have any stake in?

1313
01:57:16,098 --> 01:57:18,157
Then do it for me.

1314
01:57:19,034 --> 01:57:20,433
If you really care.

1315
01:57:20,433 --> 01:57:24,039
When you left me, I left Earth.

1316
01:57:24,039 --> 01:57:27,107
Does that not show you that I care?

1317
01:57:30,312 --> 01:57:33,247
My red world here, now...

1318
01:57:34,250 --> 01:57:37,151
...means more to me than your blue one.

1319
01:57:37,920 --> 01:57:39,649
Let me show you.

1320
01:57:57,773 --> 01:58:00,708
<i>MAN:
Bombers are fueled and ready, sir.</i>

1321
01:58:10,052 --> 01:58:12,282
It's time, gentlemen.

1322
01:58:14,390 --> 01:58:16,790
Take us to DEFCON one.

1323
01:58:22,164 --> 01:58:25,258
<i>RORSCHACH:
Not in penthouse. Not in office.</i>

1324
01:58:25,258 --> 01:58:28,335
<i>What nocturnal proclivities
entice a man with everything...</i>

1325
01:58:28,335 --> 01:58:30,267
<i>...out into the night at this hour?</i>

1326
01:58:30,267 --> 01:58:32,202
DAN:
I'm gonna look for Adrian's itinerary.

1327
01:58:32,202 --> 01:58:35,138
RORSCHACH:
Maybe he keeps on file.

1328
01:58:39,815 --> 01:58:42,283
-Something's not right.
-Agreed.

1329
01:58:42,283 --> 01:58:47,218
Janey Slater, Moloch, Roy Chess
all work for Pyramid.

1330
01:58:47,218 --> 01:58:52,019
Moloch said the Comedian mentioned list
with his and Slater’s name on it.

1331
01:58:52,019 --> 01:58:55,493
Whoever owns Pyramid
could be giving these people cancer.

1332
01:58:55,493 --> 01:58:58,132
Setting Manhattan up.

1333
01:59:09,912 --> 01:59:11,379
[BEEPING]

1334
01:59:12,281 --> 01:59:13,441
Funny.

1335
01:59:13,441 --> 01:59:17,108
Ancient pharaohs looked forward
to the end of the world.

1336
01:59:17,108 --> 01:59:22,314
Believed cadavers would rise,
reclaim hearts from golden jars.

1337
01:59:22,958 --> 01:59:25,586
Must currently be holding breath
in anticipation.

1338
01:59:25,586 --> 01:59:26,989
Pharaohs?

1339
01:59:29,865 --> 01:59:31,560
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

1340
01:59:33,869 --> 01:59:35,894
Got a psych profile on Manhattan.

1341
01:59:36,538 --> 01:59:39,006
See what the corporate head-peepers say.

1342
01:59:41,043 --> 01:59:43,568
"Subject continues
to retreat emotionally.

1343
01:59:45,881 --> 01:59:48,941
If the only remaining ties
were to be severed...

1344
01:59:49,551 --> 01:59:53,510
...we predict total detachment
from the human condition."

1345
01:59:57,626 --> 01:59:59,389
DAN:
I'm in.

1346
02:00:28,257 --> 02:00:29,588
No.

1347
02:00:31,760 --> 02:00:37,528
MAN: Congratulations, Mr. Veidt.
Dr. Manhattan's energy reactor is online.

1348
02:00:37,528 --> 02:00:41,568
Your support and your enthusiasm...

1349
02:00:41,568 --> 02:00:44,035
...is what has led to this triumph.

1350
02:00:44,035 --> 02:00:48,233
On behalf of the research team,
we salute you.

1351
02:00:48,233 --> 02:00:50,844
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

1352
02:00:51,613 --> 02:00:55,743
ADRIAN: What in life
does not deserve celebrating?

1353
02:00:56,685 --> 02:01:00,781
This is the new Karnak.

1354
02:01:00,781 --> 02:01:04,551
This represents the culmination of a dream
more than 2000 years old...

1355
02:01:04,551 --> 02:01:10,996
...a dream now assured
because of your unquestioning assistance.

1356
02:01:13,135 --> 02:01:14,796
And for this...

1357
02:01:15,637 --> 02:01:17,969
...I am ashamed...

1358
02:01:19,141 --> 02:01:23,475
...ashamed that you must now share
such inadequate a reward.

1359
02:01:25,147 --> 02:01:27,138
To the pharaohs...

1360
02:01:28,083 --> 02:01:31,075
...their greatest secrets
entrusted to their servants...

1361
02:01:31,720 --> 02:01:36,054
...buried alive with them
in sand-floored chambers.

1362
02:01:36,925 --> 02:01:39,325
Sleep well, gentlemen.

1363
02:01:39,995 --> 02:01:43,328
Our new, peaceful world
will be indebted...

1364
02:01:43,665 --> 02:01:46,225
...to your great sacrifice.

1365
02:01:47,169 --> 02:01:49,364
Bubastis.

1366
02:01:53,542 --> 02:01:56,534
<i>Rorschach's journal. Final entry.</i>

1367
02:01:56,879 --> 02:01:59,370
<i>Veidt's behind everything.</i>

1368
02:01:59,370 --> 02:02:01,140
<i>Why?</i>

1369
02:02:01,140 --> 02:02:03,375
<i>What's his endgame?</i>

1370
02:02:03,375 --> 02:02:07,215
<i>I cannot imagine
a more dangerous opponent.</i>

1371
02:02:07,423 --> 02:02:10,859
<i>Used to joke he was fast enough
to catch a bullet.</i>

1372
02:02:10,859 --> 02:02:13,927
<i>He could kill us both alone in the snow.</i>

1373
02:02:13,927 --> 02:02:17,793
<i>That's where we're going now:
Antarctica.</i>

1374
02:02:17,793 --> 02:02:20,730
<i>Whether I'm alive or dead
upon this reading...</i>

1375
02:02:20,730 --> 02:02:25,169
<i>...I hope the world survives long enough
for this journal to reach you.</i>

1376
02:02:25,169 --> 02:02:27,900
<i>I live my life free of compromise...</i>

1377
02:02:27,900 --> 02:02:32,012
<i>...and step into the shadow
without complaint or regret.</i>

1378
02:02:32,648 --> 02:02:35,640
<i>Rorschach, November 1st.</i>

1379
02:02:35,640 --> 02:02:39,345
<i>LAURIE: Can't you just tell me how
this all ends and save us the trouble?</i>

1380
02:02:40,322 --> 02:02:42,222
JON:
It ends with you in tears.

1381
02:02:42,222 --> 02:02:45,986
Tears? So you don't come back to Earth.

1382
02:02:45,986 --> 02:02:49,597
At some point, yes.

1383
02:02:50,666 --> 02:02:53,601
The streets are filled with death.

1384
02:02:53,601 --> 02:02:55,828
Jon, please.

1385
02:02:55,828 --> 02:03:00,566
You have to stop this. Everyone will die.

1386
02:03:00,566 --> 02:03:05,076
And the universe will not even notice.

1387
02:03:07,516 --> 02:03:11,748
In my opinion, the existence of life...

1388
02:03:12,621 --> 02:03:15,613
...is a highly overrated phenomenon.

1389
02:03:17,526 --> 02:03:19,824
Just look around you.

1390
02:03:22,564 --> 02:03:26,898
Mars gets along perfectly well
without so much as a microorganism.

1391
02:03:27,536 --> 02:03:32,098
Here, it's a constantly changing
topographical map...

1392
02:03:32,098 --> 02:03:38,213
...flowing and shifting around the pole
in ripples 10,000 years wide.

1393
02:03:39,047 --> 02:03:40,537
So tell me...

1394
02:03:40,537 --> 02:03:45,085
...how would all of this be greatly improved
by an oil pipeline?

1395
02:03:45,554 --> 02:03:47,545
By a shopping mall?

1396
02:03:51,894 --> 02:03:56,194
So it's too much to ask for a miracle?

1397
02:03:56,194 --> 02:03:58,492
Miracles, by their definition,
are meaningless.

1398
02:03:58,492 --> 02:04:00,157
Oh, God, Jon!

1399
02:04:00,157 --> 02:04:05,398
-Only what can happen does happen.
-Just stop your bullshit.

1400
02:04:06,475 --> 02:04:09,000
Land this thing. Now.

1401
02:04:09,000 --> 02:04:11,737
JON:
As you wish.

1402
02:04:17,352 --> 02:04:18,410
LAURIE:
You know what?

1403
02:04:18,410 --> 02:04:21,283
You can send me back to Earth
to fry with Dan and my mom...

1404
02:04:21,283 --> 02:04:23,822
...and all the other worthless humans.

1405
02:04:23,822 --> 02:04:27,428
But know that you were wrong.
You said this ended with me in tears...

1406
02:04:27,428 --> 02:04:31,760
...and look: nothing.
Maybe you were wrong about everything.

1407
02:04:31,760 --> 02:04:37,201
You complain that I refuse to see life
on life's terms...

1408
02:04:37,940 --> 02:04:41,706
...yet you continuously refuse
to see things from my perspective.

1409
02:04:41,706 --> 02:04:46,280
-You shut out what you're afraid of.
-I'm not afraid.

1410
02:04:46,280 --> 02:04:51,476
You want me to see things your way?
Go ahead, show me. Do that thing you do.

1411
02:04:58,627 --> 02:05:03,724
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
I was a hero, goddamn it!

1412
02:05:03,724 --> 02:05:06,959
It's not my fault you got old.
What do you have to complain about?

1413
02:05:06,959 --> 02:05:09,262
I am putting food on the table
for you and your child.

1414
02:05:09,262 --> 02:05:12,236
Why donot you call your friend Eddie.
Maybe he can give you a better life.

1415
02:05:12,975 --> 02:05:15,671
SALLY:
Even the grimy parts of it...

1416
02:05:16,044 --> 02:05:18,274
...keep on getting brighter.

1417
02:05:18,614 --> 02:05:20,411
You're Sally Jupiter's kid.

1418
02:05:21,316 --> 02:05:23,113
You're the Comedian, right?

1419
02:05:23,885 --> 02:05:25,614
<i>You were pretty cool in there.</i>

1420
02:05:26,021 --> 02:05:29,616
You know, your mom, she was one
of the all-time champion beauties.

1421
02:05:29,616 --> 02:05:34,228
-You got her eyes, you know. You got--
-Take your hands off her.

1422
02:05:34,228 --> 02:05:36,523
EDDIE:
Hey, doll. Long time no see.

1423
02:05:36,523 --> 02:05:39,462
Not long enough in my book, Eddie.
Get in the car.

1424
02:05:39,968 --> 02:05:40,968
Now.

1425
02:05:42,804 --> 02:05:44,795
Are there no depths you won't sink to?

1426
02:05:44,795 --> 02:05:48,807
Jesus Christ, Sally.
Can't a guy talk to his...

1427
02:05:49,511 --> 02:05:51,206
...you know, old friend's daughter?

1428
02:05:53,515 --> 02:05:54,846
Drive.

1429
02:06:00,856 --> 02:06:03,654
<i>SALLY:
It was a mistake. One time.</i>

1430
02:06:03,959 --> 02:06:07,122
Guy tries to rape you, and years later,
you let him finish the job?

1431
02:06:07,362 --> 02:06:10,058
What? Were you drunk or just lonely?

1432
02:06:10,058 --> 02:06:13,167
Am I ever gonna live this down?

1433
02:06:16,538 --> 02:06:17,664
Laurie.

1434
02:06:22,544 --> 02:06:23,875
No.

1435
02:06:25,881 --> 02:06:28,372
No, not him.

1436
02:06:28,372 --> 02:06:30,643
The Comedian...

1437
02:06:31,053 --> 02:06:33,146
...was your father.

1438
02:06:34,623 --> 02:06:35,373
No.

1439
02:06:39,628 --> 02:06:40,948
No! No! No!

1440
02:06:46,134 --> 02:06:49,035
[CRACKING]

1441
02:07:17,933 --> 02:07:19,924
My life is just...

1442
02:07:20,602 --> 02:07:22,729
...one big joke.

1443
02:07:22,729 --> 02:07:25,464
I don't think your life is a joke.

1444
02:07:27,109 --> 02:07:29,100
Yeah, well...

1445
02:07:30,946 --> 02:07:35,110
...I'm sorry if I don't
trust your sense of humor.

1446
02:07:43,291 --> 02:07:44,952
Will you smile...

1447
02:07:46,628 --> 02:07:49,096
...if I admit I was wrong?

1448
02:07:51,967 --> 02:07:53,958
LAURIE:
About what?

1449
02:07:55,971 --> 02:07:57,461
Miracles.

1450
02:07:59,141 --> 02:08:02,304
Events with astronomical odds
of occurring...

1451
02:08:03,145 --> 02:08:05,636
...like oxygen turning into gold.

1452
02:08:05,636 --> 02:08:10,649
I've longed to witness such an event,
and yet I neglect...

1453
02:08:11,319 --> 02:08:13,685
...that in human coupling...

1454
02:08:14,489 --> 02:08:18,357
...millions upon millions of cells
compete to create life...

1455
02:08:18,827 --> 02:08:21,625
...for generation after generation...

1456
02:08:22,497 --> 02:08:25,557
...until finally, your mother...

1457
02:08:25,934 --> 02:08:27,128
...loves a man...

1458
02:08:27,769 --> 02:08:31,364
...Edward Blake, the Comedian,
a man she has every reason to hate...

1459
02:08:31,364 --> 02:08:35,533
...and out of that contradiction,
against unfathomable odds...

1460
02:08:36,211 --> 02:08:38,111
...it's you--

1461
02:08:39,848 --> 02:08:41,179
Only...

1462
02:08:41,850 --> 02:08:43,340
...you.

1463
02:08:44,186 --> 02:08:45,448
--that emerged.

1464
02:08:46,021 --> 02:08:50,515
To distill so specific a form...

1465
02:08:50,515 --> 02:08:52,956
...from all that chaos...

1466
02:08:54,863 --> 02:08:57,832
...is like turning air into gold.

1467
02:09:02,204 --> 02:09:04,195
A miracle.

1468
02:09:07,709 --> 02:09:09,199
And so...

1469
02:09:09,711 --> 02:09:11,542
...I was wrong.

1470
02:09:13,548 --> 02:09:17,382
Now dry your eyes, and let's go home.

1471
02:09:44,913 --> 02:09:48,940
We got a bearing on that artificial structure.
Heat signature's off the charts.

1472
02:09:49,918 --> 02:09:53,012
-Veidt.
-I don't like the way Archie's kicking.

1473
02:10:01,429 --> 02:10:04,262
-The engines.
-They're icing up. Hold onto something.

1474
02:10:05,033 --> 02:10:07,058
Daniel, you're coming in too low.

1475
02:10:09,938 --> 02:10:13,101
Don't wish to interfere with merging of ship,
but perhaps should pull up sharply before---

1476
02:10:13,101 --> 02:10:17,211
I know! I'm trying. 
I'm trying to pull him up, goddamn it!

1477
02:10:44,472 --> 02:10:48,101
DAN: I'm gonna redirect the heat from
the flamethrower to speed up deicing...

1478
02:10:48,101 --> 02:10:51,143
...but it's gonna take a while
and we don't have time to wait.

1479
02:10:52,647 --> 02:10:54,114
You need something warmer.

1480
02:10:54,649 --> 02:10:56,810
Fine like this.

1481
02:11:25,080 --> 02:11:26,138
[BUBASTIS GROWLS]

1482
02:11:26,138 --> 02:11:28,179
What is it, girl?

1483
02:11:30,485 --> 02:11:31,235
Mm.

1484
02:11:57,779 --> 02:12:00,043
DAN:
Adrian's a pacifist.

1485
02:12:00,248 --> 02:12:04,878
He's a vegetarian, for chrissakes.
He's never killed anyone in his life.

1486
02:12:04,878 --> 02:12:06,452
Hitler was vegetarian.

1487
02:12:06,452 --> 02:12:11,149
You're squeamish, leave him to me.
We won't get second chance.

1488
02:12:16,564 --> 02:12:20,193
[CHATTERING ON TVS]

1489
02:13:22,397 --> 02:13:23,728
Gentlemen.

1490
02:13:24,232 --> 02:13:28,168
-Welcome.
-Adrian, we know everything.

1491
02:13:28,168 --> 02:13:30,099
Then what's there to discuss, Dan?

1492
02:13:30,099 --> 02:13:33,263
Plenty. You killed Comedian.

1493
02:13:33,263 --> 02:13:34,965
May he rest in peace.

1494
02:13:35,477 --> 02:13:38,071
Blake figured it out first.

1495
02:13:38,071 --> 02:13:42,307
<i>Nixon had him keeping tabs on us,
making sure we weren't rocking the boat.</i>

1496
02:13:43,251 --> 02:13:45,515
<i>Blake found out what I was doing
here in Karnak...</i>

1497
02:13:45,515 --> 02:13:49,748
<i>...and by the time he visited poor Moloch,
he was cracking badly.</i>

1498
02:13:49,748 --> 02:13:53,189
Even I couldn’t predict he'd be the one
to have a change of heart.

1499
02:13:53,928 --> 02:13:55,452
So...

1500
02:13:56,498 --> 02:13:58,432
...I had to kill him.

1501
02:13:59,000 --> 02:14:02,766
Then I neutralized Jon. No easy task.

1502
02:14:02,766 --> 02:14:05,405
I put roughly $2 billion
into tachyon research...

1503
02:14:05,405 --> 02:14:07,598
...to block Jon's vision of the future.

1504
02:14:07,598 --> 02:14:10,039
RORSCHACH: You used his psych profile
to manipulate him.

1505
02:14:10,545 --> 02:14:12,012
<i>Got him to leave the planet.</i>

1506
02:14:12,012 --> 02:14:15,581
I've known Jon long enough
to see he isn't devoid of emotion.

1507
02:14:15,581 --> 02:14:19,652
His subtle facial twitches wouldn’t be
noticed by the layman, but to me...

1508
02:14:19,652 --> 02:14:21,652
<i>...he might as well have been sobbing.</i>

1509
02:14:22,023 --> 02:14:25,151
<i>All I needed to do was tug on the thread.</i>

1510
02:14:25,151 --> 02:14:27,226
<i>The sudden flood of emotion Jon felt...</i>

1511
02:14:27,226 --> 02:14:30,990
<i>...when he came to believe
he'd given cancer to the people he loved...</i>

1512
02:14:30,990 --> 02:14:33,293
<i>...was all the excuse he needed
to leave Earth.</i>

1513
02:14:33,293 --> 02:14:37,302
<i>DAN: Your bullshit assassin.
You paid him to throw us off.</i>

1514
02:14:37,302 --> 02:14:42,136
<i>ADRIAN: Mr. Chess gave his life
in the service of a higher cause, Dan.</i>

1515
02:14:44,279 --> 02:14:47,373
<i>I put a cyanide capsule in his mouth...</i>

1516
02:14:47,373 --> 02:14:50,143
<i>...leaving only one loose end:</i>

1517
02:14:50,752 --> 02:14:54,188
You, and your mask-killer theory...

1518
02:14:54,188 --> 02:14:57,483
<i>...one you followed
with the tenacity of a true sociopath.</i>

1519
02:14:57,483 --> 02:14:59,354
<i>I tipped off the police.</i>

1520
02:14:59,354 --> 02:15:01,927
Once you were in prison,
I was able to move forward.

1521
02:15:01,927 --> 02:15:04,724
RORSCHACH:
Sorry to disappoint you.

1522
02:15:17,912 --> 02:15:20,380
DAN: We were supposed to make the world
a better place.

1523
02:15:20,380 --> 02:15:22,277
ADRIAN:
Dan, that's exactly what I am doing.

1524
02:15:22,277 --> 02:15:23,781
DAN:
Nuclear war?

1525
02:15:23,781 --> 02:15:26,113
Human extinction?

1526
02:15:35,763 --> 02:15:40,666
ADRIAN: Of course, my moral safeguards
gave me pause at the necessary sacrifice.

1527
02:15:40,666 --> 02:15:43,804
A few key regions around the globe--

1528
02:15:43,804 --> 02:15:49,433
New York, Los Angeles, Moscow,
Hong Kong.

1529
02:15:49,433 --> 02:15:51,272
--disintegrated in an instant.

1530
02:15:52,013 --> 02:15:55,346
Fifteen million people killed...

1531
02:15:55,346 --> 02:15:57,575
...by Dr. Manhattan himself.

1532
02:15:58,786 --> 02:16:01,584
The world’s punishment
for flirting with World War III.

1533
02:16:01,584 --> 02:16:02,882
Jon wouldn’t do that.

1534
02:16:03,458 --> 02:16:06,154
A fact no one outside this room
ever has to know.

1535
02:16:06,794 --> 02:16:10,594
The energy breakthrough I was working on
just came to fruition.

1536
02:16:11,199 --> 02:16:15,192
AII these years, Jon was helping me
replicate his power...

1537
02:16:15,192 --> 02:16:17,895
...unaware of how I planned to use it.

1538
02:16:17,895 --> 02:16:20,063
You see...

1539
02:16:20,975 --> 02:16:23,375
...the Comedian was right.

1540
02:16:24,078 --> 02:16:29,072
Humanity's savage nature
will inevitably lead to global annihilation.

1541
02:16:29,072 --> 02:16:32,048
So in order to save this planet...

1542
02:16:32,320 --> 02:16:34,379
...I had to trick it...

1543
02:16:34,756 --> 02:16:38,783
...with the greatest practical joke
in human history.

1544
02:16:39,060 --> 02:16:42,461
-Killing millions.
-To save billions.

1545
02:16:42,997 --> 02:16:44,965
A necessary crime.

1546
02:16:44,965 --> 02:16:47,294
RORSCHACH:
You know we can't let you do that.

1547
02:16:48,736 --> 02:16:50,863
"Do that," Rorschach?

1548
02:16:50,863 --> 02:16:52,666
I'm not a comic-book villain.

1549
02:16:53,508 --> 02:16:55,772
Do you seriously think
I'd explain my masterstroke to you...

1550
02:16:55,772 --> 02:17:00,107
...if there were even the slightest possibility
you could affect the outcome?

1551
02:17:02,850 --> 02:17:05,648
I triggered it 35 minutes ago.

1552
02:18:45,119 --> 02:18:48,111
Jesus Christ, Henry.

1553
02:18:48,111 --> 02:18:50,484
Why the hell
didn't we get a launch detection?

1554
02:18:52,393 --> 02:18:56,830
It's not the Soviets, sir.

1555
02:18:57,398 --> 02:19:00,561
Intel indicates the energy signature...

1556
02:19:00,561 --> 02:19:03,169
...was generated by...

1557
02:19:04,138 --> 02:19:06,572
...Dr. Manhattan.

1558
02:19:09,410 --> 02:19:10,968
Jon.

1559
02:19:13,981 --> 02:19:15,107
Interference.

1560
02:19:15,716 --> 02:19:17,616
Cataclysmic interference.

1561
02:19:27,328 --> 02:19:30,092
LAURIE:
I can't believe it happened.

1562
02:19:31,098 --> 02:19:34,590
This wasn't caused by nuclear warheads.

1563
02:19:38,673 --> 02:19:39,970
It was me.

1564
02:19:42,009 --> 02:19:43,601
I...

1565
02:19:44,178 --> 02:19:45,202
...did this.

1566
02:19:45,847 --> 02:19:49,305
-What do you mean, you did this?
-Not directly.

1567
02:19:50,284 --> 02:19:52,980
It was made to look like I did it.

1568
02:19:56,023 --> 02:19:57,456
Adrian.

1569
02:20:03,731 --> 02:20:05,722
Speak of the devil.

1570
02:20:08,870 --> 02:20:09,894
DAN: Jon--
JON: I know.

1571
02:20:09,894 --> 02:20:12,232
RORSCHACH: Must stop him.
Killed Blake, killed millions.

1572
02:20:12,232 --> 02:20:13,737
Wait here.

1573
02:20:24,886 --> 02:20:27,252
Adrian, stop this.

1574
02:20:28,723 --> 02:20:30,588
The tachyons were clever...

1575
02:20:31,726 --> 02:20:36,060
...but even if I can't predict where you are,
I can turn the walls to glass.

1576
02:20:37,398 --> 02:20:39,866
I should thank you.

1577
02:20:41,035 --> 02:20:44,232
I'd almost forgotten the excitement
of not knowing...

1578
02:20:45,239 --> 02:20:48,231
<i>...the delights of uncertainty.</i>

1579
02:20:52,413 --> 02:20:54,074
Forgive me, girl.

1580
02:21:14,602 --> 02:21:16,069
[GUN COCKS]

1581
02:21:17,038 --> 02:21:18,733
You're such an asshole.

1582
02:21:49,103 --> 02:21:50,331
[GASPS]

1583
02:21:52,673 --> 02:21:54,607
DAN:
Veidt, you bastard.

1584
02:21:54,607 --> 02:21:57,243
-If you've hurt her, I'II--
-Dan...

1585
02:21:58,980 --> 02:22:03,576
...grow up. My new world
demands less obvious heroism.

1586
02:22:03,576 --> 02:22:05,742
Your...

1587
02:22:05,742 --> 02:22:10,880
...schoolboy heroics are redundant.
What have they achieved?

1588
02:22:12,493 --> 02:22:15,360
Failing to prevent Earth's salivation...

1589
02:22:16,330 --> 02:22:18,730
...is your only triumph.

1590
02:22:18,933 --> 02:22:20,833
JON:
I'm disappointed in you, Adrian.

1591
02:22:21,636 --> 02:22:25,128
I'm very disappointed.

1592
02:22:37,518 --> 02:22:40,681
Reassembling myself
was the first trick I learned.

1593
02:22:41,355 --> 02:22:43,755
It didn't kill Osterman.

1594
02:22:46,360 --> 02:22:48,726
Did you really think it would kill me?

1595
02:22:50,031 --> 02:22:53,194
I have walked across the surface
of the sun.

1596
02:22:53,701 --> 02:22:56,864
I have witnessed events
so tiny and so fast...

1597
02:22:56,864 --> 02:23:00,098
...they can hardly be said
to have occurred at all...

1598
02:23:00,098 --> 02:23:03,903
...but you, Adrian, you're just a man.

1599
02:23:05,046 --> 02:23:07,537
The world’s smartest man...

1600
02:23:07,537 --> 02:23:10,275
...poses no more threat to me...

1601
02:23:10,275 --> 02:23:13,579
...than does its smartest termite.

1602
02:23:15,856 --> 02:23:17,323
What's that?

1603
02:23:17,725 --> 02:23:19,590
Another ultimate weapon?

1604
02:23:20,227 --> 02:23:21,956
Yes.

1605
02:23:23,564 --> 02:23:25,031
You could say that.

1606
02:23:28,569 --> 02:23:30,503
<i>--came under attack.</i>

1607
02:23:31,338 --> 02:23:34,671
<i>Millions of lives were suddenly ended...</i>

1608
02:23:35,009 --> 02:23:40,208
<i>...in an act of evil
perpetrated by Dr. Manhattan himself.</i>

1609
02:23:42,016 --> 02:23:45,952
<i>Since the attacks,
I have been in constant contact...</i>

1610
02:23:45,952 --> 02:23:49,112
<i>...with the premier of the U.S.S.R.</i>

1611
02:23:49,523 --> 02:23:52,356
<i>Putting aside our past differences...</i>

1612
02:23:52,693 --> 02:23:54,854
<i>...we have both pledged to unite...</i>

1613
02:23:55,196 --> 02:23:58,529
<i>...against this common enemy.</i>

1614
02:23:59,033 --> 02:24:01,024
<i>With the rest of the world...</i>

1615
02:24:01,469 --> 02:24:03,494
<i>...we will prevail.</i>

1616
02:24:06,040 --> 02:24:09,032
<i>This is a day we shall never forget.</i>

1617
02:24:09,032 --> 02:24:13,408
<i>And yet we go forward
to defend the human race...</i>

1618
02:24:13,408 --> 02:24:18,211
<i>...and all that is good
and just in our world.</i>

1619
02:24:19,553 --> 02:24:23,785
<i>Thank you. God bless us all.</i>

1620
02:24:24,158 --> 02:24:25,955
ADRIAN:
Do you see?

1621
02:24:28,162 --> 02:24:30,630
Two superpowers retreating from war.

1622
02:24:32,233 --> 02:24:34,667
I've saved the earth from hell.

1623
02:24:34,667 --> 02:24:36,803
We both have.

1624
02:24:37,271 --> 02:24:39,466
This is as much your victory as it is mine.

1625
02:24:44,278 --> 02:24:45,768
Now we can return...

1626
02:24:47,214 --> 02:24:48,772
...do what we were meant to.

1627
02:24:48,772 --> 02:24:51,918
We were meant to exact justice.

1628
02:24:52,253 --> 02:24:55,586
-Everyone's gonna know what you've done.
-Will they?

1629
02:24:55,586 --> 02:25:00,557
By exposing me, you would sacrifice
the peace so many died for today.

1630
02:25:00,557 --> 02:25:04,164
-Peace based on a lie.
-But peace...

1631
02:25:04,164 --> 02:25:06,526
-...nonetheless.
-He's right.

1632
02:25:07,101 --> 02:25:11,060
Exposing Adrian would only doom the world
to nuclear destruction again.

1633
02:25:11,060 --> 02:25:14,105
No. We can't do this.

1634
02:25:14,105 --> 02:25:16,038
On Mars...

1635
02:25:17,545 --> 02:25:19,376
...you taught me the value of life.

1636
02:25:20,347 --> 02:25:22,781
If we hope to preserve it here...

1637
02:25:23,584 --> 02:25:25,609
...we must remain silent.

1638
02:25:29,456 --> 02:25:31,390
Keep your own secrets.

1639
02:25:38,265 --> 02:25:39,459
Don't even think about it.

1640
02:25:42,069 --> 02:25:43,798
Rorschach.

1641
02:25:45,573 --> 02:25:47,097
Wait.

1642
02:25:48,142 --> 02:25:50,235
Never compromise.

1643
02:25:50,611 --> 02:25:53,478
Not even in the face of Armageddon.

1644
02:25:53,881 --> 02:25:56,873
That's always been the difference
between us, Daniel.

1645
02:26:07,928 --> 02:26:11,455
I've made myself feel every death...

1646
02:26:12,933 --> 02:26:18,838
...see every innocent face
I've murdered to save humanity.

1647
02:26:24,411 --> 02:26:28,108
-You understand, don't you?
JON: Without condoning...

1648
02:26:29,783 --> 02:26:31,683
...or condemning...

1649
02:26:36,090 --> 02:26:38,024
...I understand.

1650
02:26:45,432 --> 02:26:48,560
Out of my way. People have to be told.

1651
02:26:49,436 --> 02:26:51,370
You know I can't let you do that.

1652
02:26:52,606 --> 02:26:55,598
Suddenly you discover humanity?

1653
02:26:57,044 --> 02:26:58,875
Convenient.

1654
02:27:07,588 --> 02:27:12,150
If you'd cared from the start,
none of this would have happened.

1655
02:27:15,930 --> 02:27:18,899
I can change almost anything...

1656
02:27:23,470 --> 02:27:25,802
...but I can't change human nature.

1657
02:27:27,141 --> 02:27:30,542
Of course
you must protect Veidt's new utopia.

1658
02:27:31,812 --> 02:27:35,145
What's one more body
amongst foundations?

1659
02:27:41,322 --> 02:27:43,187
Well, what are you waiting for?

1660
02:27:46,660 --> 02:27:48,491
Do it.

1661
02:27:54,601 --> 02:27:55,625
Do it!

1662
02:27:58,339 --> 02:27:59,089
No!

1663
02:28:19,193 --> 02:28:24,961
<i>JON: I'm leaving this galaxy
for one a little less complicated.</i>

1664
02:28:24,961 --> 02:28:27,623
<i>LAURIE: I thought you said you cared
about life again.</i>

1665
02:28:27,623 --> 02:28:29,200
<i>JON:
I do.</i>

1666
02:28:30,537 --> 02:28:33,438
I think maybe I'II create some.

1667
02:28:37,544 --> 02:28:39,876
Goodbye, Laurie.

1668
02:28:59,767 --> 02:29:02,998
[DAN YELLING]

1669
02:29:15,115 --> 02:29:16,275
Come on.

1670
02:29:18,752 --> 02:29:20,344
Come on!

1671
02:29:24,758 --> 02:29:26,089
Dan...

1672
02:29:26,560 --> 02:29:29,324
...a world united and at peace.

1673
02:29:30,197 --> 02:29:31,391
There had to be sacrifice.

1674
02:29:31,391 --> 02:29:35,934
No! You haven't idealized mankind,
but you've deformed it.

1675
02:29:35,934 --> 02:29:37,866
You've mutilated it.

1676
02:29:38,238 --> 02:29:40,399
That's your legacy.

1677
02:29:48,949 --> 02:29:51,747
That's the real practical joke.

1678
02:30:44,338 --> 02:30:48,331
<i>MAN [ON TV] : We repeat, there is
nothing wrong with your television set.</i>

1679
02:30:48,331 --> 02:30:51,967
<i>You are about to participate
in a great adventure.</i>

1680
02:30:51,967 --> 02:30:55,309
<i>You are about to experience
the awe and mystery...</i>

1681
02:30:55,309 --> 02:31:01,284
<i>...which reaches from the inner mind
to the outer limits.</i>

1682
02:31:02,489 --> 02:31:04,684
SALLY:
Sure you don't want a drink?

1683
02:31:05,692 --> 02:31:06,716
I'm okay.

1684
02:31:07,794 --> 02:31:09,022
Cheers.

1685
02:31:10,464 --> 02:31:13,592
There's something I need
to get off my chest.

1686
02:31:14,868 --> 02:31:17,359
I know that Eddie Blake was my father.

1687
02:31:20,374 --> 02:31:22,137
Laurel.

1688
02:31:23,143 --> 02:31:25,475
What you must think of me.

1689
02:31:26,313 --> 02:31:28,838
I'm sorry I never told you.

1690
02:31:28,838 --> 02:31:30,813
I should have but...

1691
02:31:30,813 --> 02:31:35,114
...I don't know, I just felt ashamed.
I felt stupid.

1692
02:31:35,114 --> 02:31:37,223
It doesn't matter.

1693
02:31:38,058 --> 02:31:43,325
People’s lives take them strange places.
They do strange things...

1694
02:31:43,897 --> 02:31:46,832
...and, well,
sometimes they can't talk about them.

1695
02:31:46,832 --> 02:31:49,332
I know how that is...

1696
02:31:50,070 --> 02:31:52,664
...but I just want you to know...

1697
02:31:53,240 --> 02:31:56,073
...that you never did anything wrong
by me.

1698
02:32:00,247 --> 02:32:04,513
You asked me why I wasn't mad at him.

1699
02:32:06,086 --> 02:32:08,577
Because he gave me you.

1700
02:32:13,594 --> 02:32:14,686
Thanks, Mom.

1701
02:32:17,431 --> 02:32:19,228
I love you.

1702
02:32:26,773 --> 02:32:30,971
-Hello, Miss Jupiter.
-Oh, Sally, please.

1703
02:32:32,613 --> 02:32:37,209
Excuse me. Gotta go freshen up.
I'II be right back.

1704
02:32:47,728 --> 02:32:51,892
-So how's it going up here?
-Good. How's it going down there?

1705
02:32:51,892 --> 02:32:55,557
Good. I think I've got everything working.

1706
02:32:55,557 --> 02:33:00,366
AII of Archie's systems are upgraded.
Finished the tinkering for now...

1707
02:33:00,366 --> 02:33:02,770
...so all we gotta do is take her out.

1708
02:33:02,770 --> 02:33:06,003
Well, that sounds like a date.

1709
02:33:17,324 --> 02:33:19,588
Are we gonna be all right?

1710
02:33:21,662 --> 02:33:25,962
Long as people think Jon's
still watching us, we’ll be all right...

1711
02:33:26,166 --> 02:33:28,031
...in the end.

1712
02:33:29,670 --> 02:33:31,831
I know what Jon would say:

1713
02:33:31,831 --> 02:33:34,030
Nothing ends.

1714
02:33:35,942 --> 02:33:38,536
Nothing ever ends.

1715
02:34:25,892 --> 02:34:29,658
Seymour, we got nothing
to write about anymore.

1716
02:34:29,658 --> 02:34:31,195
Everyone in the country...

1717
02:34:31,195 --> 02:34:33,629
...every country in the world
are holding hands...

1718
02:34:33,629 --> 02:34:37,065
...and singing songs
about peace and love.

1719
02:34:37,571 --> 02:34:40,438
It's like living in a goddamn
global hippie commune.

1720
02:34:40,438 --> 02:34:44,543
Well, Ronald Reagan says he's gonna
be running for president in '88.

1721
02:34:44,543 --> 02:34:46,542
We could run a piece on that.

1722
02:34:46,542 --> 02:34:49,876
Seymour, we don't dignify absurdities
with coverage.

1723
02:34:49,876 --> 02:34:53,884
This is still America, damn it.
Who wants a cowboy in the White House?

1724
02:34:54,621 --> 02:34:58,853
Okay. I could look for something
in the crank file.

1725
02:34:58,853 --> 02:35:00,617
Crank file.

1726
02:35:00,617 --> 02:35:02,785
Whatever. Take some initiative.

1727
02:35:02,785 --> 02:35:05,591
Run whatever you like.
I leave it entirely in your hands.

1728
02:35:12,105 --> 02:35:16,804
<i>Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.</i>

1729
02:35:16,804 --> 02:35:21,437
<i>Tonight, a comedian died in New York.</i>

